\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid92027 19. CLOTHING}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484735 
\par 
\par Clothing continues the subject of much concern - footwear problems, in particular, in view of the coming winter months.
\par 
\par Increased coupon values for leather-soled shoes: (No reactions have been received to the announcement of extra coupons 
for children with big feet.) During the past two weeks there has been widespread criticism and resentment at the increased coupon Values for loather-soled shoes (Thirteen Regions). Parents of growing children who take adult sizes, and who are not tall eno
ugh to qualify for extra coupons, are especially upset (Six Regions): "Boy's size 5 only}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5447783  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484735 require three coupons, but size 5 1/2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11892501  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484735 now require nine coupons".
\par 
\par People are said to have felt that even the old number was too high in view of the poor wearing qualities of present day shoes. It is claimed that a reduction rather than an increase in the coupon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5447783  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484735 value of adult leather-soled shoes should have been made. (Three Regions)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid92027 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484735 (1.2.3.4.5.5SE.6.7.8.9.10.11.13.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11892501  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484735 17 four provincial P.Cs.)
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid92027 20. FOOD}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484735 
\par 
\par Sa
tisfaction with the food situation continues, although there is again some grumbling about the distribution and prices of certain commodities. The shortage of fruit (Six Regions) and of tomatoes (Three Regions) and the high prices of vegetables (Three Reg
ions) and of fruit (Two Regions) are particularly criticised. People are asking "where is the bumper crop of plums".
\par 
\par From Scotland, it is reported that "public anger is strong concerning the dumping of herrings at Clydeside ports last week. Press repor
ts of conferences on the subject only increase the anger. 'It's a pure scandal' is one of the milder comments on the situation People are talking about this everywhere." From Co. Durham it is also reported: "There is a glut of fish, but here we have a fam
ine".
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid92027 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484735 (1.2.3.4.5.5SE.6.7.8.10.11.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11892501  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484735 17 nine provincial P.Cs.) 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid92027 21. AGRICULTURE}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484735 
\par 
\par The bumper harvest is praised this week in three Regional reports and Postal Censorship. In Wales, Devon and Cornwall, farmers complain that "the weather has been against them".
\par 
\par Though some farmers still report shortage of labour, others speak of voluntary help "willingly and enthusiastically given".
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid92027 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484735 (1.3.5SE.7.8.10.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11892501  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484735 17 four provincial P.Cs.)
\par 
